If $${a_1},{a_2},{a_3},.........,{a_n},......$$ are in G.P., then the value of the determinant 
<p>$$\left| {\matrix{
   {\log {a_n}} &amp; {\log {a_{n + 1}}} &amp; {\log {a_{n + 2}}}  \cr 
   {\log {a_{n + 3}}} &amp; {\log {a_{n + 4}}} &amp; {\log {a_{n + 5}}}  \cr 
   {\log {a_{n + 6}}} &amp; {\log {a_{n + 7}}} &amp; {\log {a_{n + 8}}}  \cr 

 } } \right|,$$ is </p>

questions.explanation:
$$\left| {\matrix{
   {\log {a_n}} &amp; {\log {a_{n + 1}}} &amp; {\log {a_{n + 2}}}  \cr 
   {\log {a_{n + 3}}} &amp; {\log {a_{n + 4}}} &amp; {\log {a_{n + 5}}}  \cr 
   {\log {a_{n + 6}}} &amp; {\log {a_{n + 7}}} &amp; {\log {a_{n + 8}}}  \cr 

 } } \right|$$
<br><br>$$ = \left| {\matrix{
   {\log {a_1}r{}^{n - 1}} &amp; {\log {a_1}r{}^n} &amp; {\log {a_1}r{}^{n + 1}}  \cr 
   {\log {a_1}r{}^{n + 2}} &amp; {\log {a_1}r{}^{n + 3}} &amp; {\log {a_1}r{}^{n + 4}}  \cr 
   {\log {a_1}r{}^{n + 5}} &amp; {\log {a_1}r{}^{n + 6}} &amp; {\log {a_1}r{}^{n + 7}}  \cr 

 } } \right|$$
<br><br>$$ = \left| {\matrix{
   {\log {a_1} + \left( {n - 1} \right)\log r} &amp; {\log {a_1} + n\log r} &amp; {\log {a_1} + \left( {n + 1} \right)\log r}  \cr 
   {\log {a_1} + \left( {n + 2} \right)\log r} &amp; {\log {a_1} + \left( {n + 3} \right)\log r} &amp; {\log {a_1} + \left( {n + 4} \right)\log r}  \cr 
   {\log {a_1} + \left( {n + 5} \right)\log r} &amp; {\log {a_1} + \left( {n + 6} \right)\log r} &amp; {\log {a_1} + \left( {n + 7} \right)\log r}  \cr 

 } } \right|$$
<br><br>$$ = 0\left[ \, \right.$$ Apply $$\,\,\,\,{c_2} \to {c_2} - {1 \over 2}{c_1} - {1 \over 2}{c_3}\,\left. \, \right]$$
